o Antiviruspoint. Antiviruspoint reserves the right to, at its sole discretion, terminate (including: ban, delete, etc) your user account without prior notice for any reasons included within these Terms or otherwise.</p><p>By signing up for a Website user account, you agree that you have no actual ownership of your account or any portion of this Website. Antiviruspoint may, at its discretion and without prior notice, remove any or all material submitted by your account (including the account itself) for reasons including but not limited to: violation of these Terms, violation of US, Canadian or international law, troublemaking, etc. Antiviruspoint assumes no liability for any content or service removed from our site, whether it originated from Antiviruspoint or a Website user account, and reserves the right to permanently restrict or block access to the Website or a user account. By using this Website, you agree that Antiviruspoint will have no liability to you if this Website and its content and services are discontinued to you or in general.</p><p>Ownership of Website Content and Intellectual Property</p><p>The content and intellectual property on this Website belongs to Antiviruspoint or attributed Antiviruspoint content providers and licensees and protected under Canadian and international law. Content includes but is not limited to: information, data, images, video, trademarks, service marks, industrial designs, logo, and other material and services, both copyrighted and non-copyrighted.</p><p>\"Antiviruspoint\" and all associated trademarks, service marks, ownership designations and logos are the property of Antiviruspoint. Such markings may not be used without the explicit written permission of Antiviruspoint. You may not combine or otherwise modify Antiviruspoint markings to affiliate the Antiviruspoint markings with that of another party to imply a relationship between Antiviruspoint and the other party. All other trademarks, logos or slogans not owned by \